results.name: a(n) = number of positive integers k, k <= n, where d(k) >= d(n); d(n) = number of positive divisors of n.
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
example: 9 has 3 positive divisors. Among the first 9 positive integers, there are four that have more than or equal the number of divisors than 9 has: 4, with 3 divisors; 6, with 4 divisors; 8, with 4 divisors; and 9, with 3 divisors. So a(9) = 4.
program: (PARI) a(n) = my(dn=numdiv(n)); sum(k=1, n, numdiv(k) >= dn); \\ _Michel Marcus_, Sep 26 2018
results.author: _Leroy Quet_, Feb 27 2008
